Orc Weapon Expertise			KEY:Warpriest Bonus Feat ~ Orc Weapon Expertise			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warpriest Bonus Feat																																														PRERACE:1,Orc,RACESUBTYPE=Orc																											PRETOTALAB:1													DESC:You can do more with the weapons orcs favor the most.																																														STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE																																																																													ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Orc Weapon Expertise (%LIST)	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Orc Weapon Expertise|1																						SOURCEPAGE:p.142																		BENEFIT:Whenever you wield a weapon that has "orc" in its name, you gain the benefit you chose so long as you are actually proficient with that weapon. This feat has no effect if you are not proficient with the weapon you're using.  You can gain this feat multiple times. Each time you take this feat, you must choose a different benefit. You may only apply one of these benefits per round (chosen as a free action at the start of your turn).
Reverse-Feint				KEY:Warpriest Bonus Feat ~ Reverse-Feint				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warpriest Bonus Feat	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Toughness																																							PRERACE:1,Orc,RACESUBTYPE=Orc																											PRETOTALAB:1													DESC:You can goad an opponent into attacking you in order to make your counter attack all the more powerful.																																																																																																																								ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Reverse-Feint																																SOURCEPAGE:p.142																		BENEFIT:As a move action, you can leave a gap in your defenses for one adjacent opponent to use. If the opponent attacks you on its next turn, it gains a +4 bonus on its attack roll. Whether or not the opponent successfully hits, you may attack it as an immediate action with a single melee attack, gaining a +2 bonus on your attack roll.
